            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Analysis and Differential Equations "
                    }
                ],
                "level": 1
            },
            "bbox": [
                289,
                156,
                707,
                177
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 1. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "Q : \\mathbb { R }  \\mathbb { R }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be a "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "C _ { c } ^ { \\infty }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "function, i.e. it is smooth and has compact support. We assume "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "Q"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is even, i.e. "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "Q ( x ) = Q ( - x )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". We assume "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "Q"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is non-trivial, (i.e. "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "Q"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "does not equal to zero everywhere). "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                129,
                203,
                865,
                247
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "T _ { 1 } ( x ) : = x Q ( x )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", and let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "T _ { 2 } ( x ) = x ^ { 2 } Q ( x )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "T _ { 3 } : = e ^ { - x ^ { 2 } } ( 1 + x ^ { 2 0 2 4 } )"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                154,
                258,
                682,
                275
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "We also introduce the following notation. For any "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f : \\mathbb { R } \\to \\mathbb { R }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\lambda > 0 , \\alpha \\in \\mathbb { R }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", we define "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                129,
                275,
                759,
                288
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "f _ {\\lambda , \\alpha} (x) := \\frac {1}{\\lambda^ {1 / 2}} f \\left(\\frac {x - \\alpha}{\\lambda}\\right) \\tag {0.1}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/a253df0d8a026502e6f74506c400a37cd0adb7c76b224b9ade128954e90b3f85.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                406,
                299,
                862,
                326
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "We claim: There exists "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\delta > 0 , \\epsilon > 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", so that for any "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "c \\in \\mathbb { R }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "| c | < \\delta"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", one can find unique "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\lambda , \\alpha"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "such that the followings hold "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                129,
                336,
                863,
                365
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "1. "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "| \\lambda - 1 | + | \\alpha | < \\epsilon"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ". "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "2. ă Qλ,α ´ Q ´ cT3, T1 ą“ 0 "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "3. ă Qλ,α ´ Q ´ cT3, T2 ą“ 0 "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                151,
                374,
                394,
                436
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(Here, for any two functions "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f _ { 1 } , f _ { 2 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", we define "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "< f _ { 1 } , f _ { 2 } > : = \\int f _ { 1 } ( x ) f _ { 2 } ( x ) d x )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                129,
                444,
                677,
                458
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Is the above claim correct? Prove your conclusion. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                129,
                458,
                505,
                473
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 2 Recall for every "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f \\in L ^ { 2 } ( \\mathbb { R } ^ { 3 } )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", one has that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "g ( x ) : = ( - \\Delta + 1 ) ^ { - 1 } f"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is a well-defined "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "L ^ { 2 } ( \\mathbb { R } ^ { 3 } )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "function. And one may compute "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "g"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "by solving "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                129,
                486,
                863,
                517
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "(- \\Delta + 1) g = f \\tag {0.2}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/7ad90797c5aa3aa1977929c58b3195ac6ee7e1f879a5b3271c4f122b5b3493cb.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                442,
                527,
                862,
                543
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(Recall "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\Delta"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbb { R } ^ { 3 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is defined as "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\textstyle \\Delta : = \\sum _ { i = 1 } ^ { 3 } \\hat { \\sigma } _ { i } ^ { 2 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", also recall one may also define "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( - \\Delta + 1 ) ^ { - 1 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "by Fourier theory.) "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                129,
                552,
                862,
                583
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Now, let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "V ( x ) : = e ^ { - | x | ^ { 2 } }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x \\in \\mathbb { R } ^ { 3 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Prove that the operator "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "T : = I + ( - \\Delta + 1 ) ^ { - 1 } V"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is invertible in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "L ^ { 2 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                129,
                583,
                862,
                612
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\left(\\text {H e r e}, T f := f + (- \\Delta + 1) ^ {- 1} (V f).\\right)",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/9142ec5243fa95de333dafdee502c71553abbb93565930942976c70080f8727b.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                157,
                613,
                425,
                629
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 3 Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\psi ( \\xi ) \\in C _ { c } ^ { \\infty } ( \\mathbb { R } )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be smooth and has compact support. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\psi ( \\xi ) = 0 , \\forall | \\xi | \\geqslant 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f _ { 1 } ( \\xi ) , f _ { 2 } ( \\xi ) \\in C _ { c } ^ { \\infty } ( \\mathbb { R } )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", i.e. "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f _ { 1 } , f _ { 2 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are smooth and have compact support. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "u _ { i } : \\mathbb { R } \\times \\mathbb { R } \\to \\mathbb { C }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "i = 1 , 2"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", be defined as "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                129,
                640,
                863,
                683
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "u _ {1} \\left(x _ {1}, x _ {2}\\right) := \\int_ {\\mathbb {R}} \\psi (\\xi) f _ {1} (\\xi) e ^ {i \\xi x _ {1}} e ^ {i \\xi^ {2} x _ {2}} d \\xi , \\tag {0.3}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/10fb5e87ac0940e55dba923556d40e111d1b553770bf72568c9e522cedef9854.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                337,
                684,
                860,
                720
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "u _ {2} \\left(x _ {1}, x _ {2}\\right) := \\int_ {\\mathbb {R}} \\psi (\\eta - 1 0) f _ {2} (\\eta) e ^ {i \\eta x _ {1}} e ^ {i \\eta^ {2} x _ {2}} d \\eta",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/8eaeccbf00e57bb73cf43b80fb83538fa81cb8941f4f98ee52dd66cd5f12ccfb.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                337,
                713,
                660,
                744
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Prove there exists a constant "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "C"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", which may depend on "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\psi"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", but does not depend on "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f _ { 1 } , f _ { 2 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", so that "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                129,
                749,
                843,
                764
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\left\\| u _ {1} u _ {2} \\right\\| _ {L ^ {2} \\left(\\mathbb {R} ^ {2}\\right)} \\leqslant C \\| f _ {1} \\| _ {L ^ {2} (\\mathbb {R})} \\| f _ {2} \\| _ {L ^ {2} (\\mathbb {R})}. \\tag {0.4}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/a3f0e952748642d15cab33ef0fcb55b9a7b2cfd03fa06a47996eb03be2222f84.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                366,
                775,
                862,
                791
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(Hint: One may try to use Plancherel Theorem. It may be useful to observe that if one let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "H ( \\xi , \\eta ) = f _ { 1 } ( \\xi ) f _ { 2 } ( \\eta )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", then "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\| H \\| _ { L ^ { 2 } ( \\mathbb { R } ^ { 2 } ) }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are also bounded by "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\| f _ { 1 } \\| _ { L ^ { 2 } ( \\mathbb { R } ) } \\| f _ { 2 } \\| _ { L ^ { 2 } ( \\mathbb { R } ) } )"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                129,
                800,
                862,
                831
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "page_number",
            "content": {
                "page_number_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "1 "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                850,
                96,
                862,
                107
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 4 Consider the heat equation in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbb { R } ^ { 2 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "u = u ( t , x )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is a solution to "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                156,
                136,
                739,
                151
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\left\\{ \\begin{array}{l} \\frac {\\partial u}{\\partial t} - \\Delta u = 0; \\\\ u | _ {t = 0} = u _ {0} \\in L ^ {2}. \\end{array} \\right.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/15b5a59abbbf2e85bfd88537618c9f8e129f15f58ac94185f299dc4fd81a0690.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                415,
                162,
                549,
                206
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Then there exists a universal constant "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "C"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "such that "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                131,
                217,
                509,
                230
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\int_ {0} ^ {\\infty} \\| u (t) \\| _ {L ^ {\\infty}} ^ {2} d t \\leqslant C \\| u _ {0} \\| _ {L ^ {2}} ^ {2}.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/d9694d5604e76b74295c5f92a77c7e12f5de52f11b5279ecfe9f514b2aab6c70.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                384,
                239,
                579,
                269
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 5 . Consider the Fourier transform. Let "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                156,
                279,
                532,
                292
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "Q (g, f) (x) := \\int_ {\\mathbb {R} ^ {N}} \\int_ {\\mathbf {S} ^ {N - 1}} B (| x - y |, \\frac {x - y}{| x - y |} \\cdot \\sigma) g (y ^ {\\prime}) f (x ^ {\\prime}) d \\sigma d y,",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/0eba35e4bcda382d75b43ae0239fd81de2169c488c8e2d70d6dae99c85cc051d.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                273,
                300,
                722,
                331
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "B"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is a given two variable function, "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { S } ^ { N - 1 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "stands for the unit sphere in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbb { R } ^ { N }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                131,
                342,
                759,
                357
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "x ^ {\\prime} := \\frac {x + y}{2} + \\frac {| x - y | \\sigma}{2}; \\quad y ^ {\\prime} := \\frac {x + y}{2} - \\frac {| x - y | \\sigma}{2}. \\tag {0.5}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/0f98e7685c6b956937dd49138c41208f6516eab34b050682acf2f4694d87559f.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                299,
                369,
                860,
                395
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Then "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                131,
                405,
                174,
                418
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\widehat {Q (g , f)} (\\xi) = (2 \\pi) ^ {- N / 2} \\int_ {\\mathbb {R} ^ {N} \\times \\mathbf {S} ^ {N - 1}} \\hat {B} (| \\eta |, \\frac {\\xi}{| \\xi |} \\cdot \\sigma) \\hat {g} (\\xi^ {-} + \\eta) \\hat {f} (\\xi^ {+} - \\eta) d \\sigma d \\eta ,",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/b15906d9bbffe77cc9e4451104e24b208eaeb2ec28d3097a5db915373719e51f.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                221,
                428,
                742,
                458
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\begin{array} { r } { \\hat { B } ( | \\eta | , t ) : = \\int _ { \\mathbb { R } ^ { N } } B ( | q | , t ) e ^ { - i q \\cdot \\eta } d q } \\end{array}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    },
